            "label": "資料解説",
            "value": "2016文化財ウィーク(52)「大星から武器類一式の調達を依頼された回船屋・天河（川）屋義平は、女房と離縁し、我が子の命にかえても秘密を守ろうとします。ここでの名台詞(めいせりふ)が「天河屋義平は男でござる」。武士に劣らぬ町人の義心が感じられるこの段は、江戸時代に非常に人気がありました。物語はフィクションで、モデルは実在する大坂の商人の天野屋利兵衛ともいわれています。しかし、彼と赤穂藩との関係は見出されていません。（Kanadehon Ch?shingura"
        },
        {
            "label": "資料解説",
            "value": "Act 10）Shipping merchant Amagawaya Gihei"
        },
        {
            "label": "資料解説",
            "value": "who has been commissioned by ?boshi to procure all of the weapons and equipment for the revenge plot"
        },
        {
            "label": "資料解説",
            "value": "has divorced his wife and is even prepared to forfeit the life of his own children to keep the plot a secret. In this scene"
        },
        {
            "label": "資料解説",
            "value": "he recites the famous line “Amagawaya Gihei is a man of honor.” This act of the play demonstrated that the honorable spirit of commoners was in no way inferior to that of the samurai"
        },
        {
            "label": "資料解説",
            "value": "and was subsequently very popular during the Edo period.」"
        }
    ],
